news.title: Rebate period for property taxpayers starts today in Chandigarh
news.para: Owners of residential properties will get 20% rebate on the total tax amount, while owners of commercial properties will be able to avail 10% rebate if they pay during the two-month rebate period.

news.title: Building permit revenue drops by 53% within a year in Thiruvananthapuram
news.para: Lack of optimism is evident in the estimate expected for 2022-23, as well as the estimated amount from collection of building permit fee is set at Rs 20 crore; even lesser than what was expected during the previous fiscal.

news.title: Rajasthan: Now, deposit urban development tax by June 30
news.para: The government has fixed the provision of 50% rebate on principal arrears and 100% rebate on penalty on deposit of house tax on residential/commercial plots/buildings from April 1, 2022 to June 30, 2022.

news.title: Max Ventures case: NCLT adjourns hearing over Neelu Analjit Singh's petition
news.para: Senior advocate Guru Krishna Kumar, appearing for Neelu Analjit Singh informed the bench that they have received a reply from Max Ventures Investment Holdings and sought a week's time to file a rejoinder over it.

news.title: Over Rs 1,131-crore stamp duty collected in March in Mumbai
news.para: The performance has surpassed the previous high of Rs 875 crore touched in March 2021, when homebuyers had taken advantage of lower stamp duty benefit.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC's property tax collection up by 10% in a year
news.para: Last time, owing to the pandemic, the BMC was able to collect Rs 5,090 crore as property tax till the end of the financial year which this time it hoped to surpass with the Covid situation in the city coming under control.

news.title: Telangana HC notice to Ramky group over Dharani fraud plea
news.para: Justice B Vijaysen Reddy ordered notices while hearing a petition filed by Yatam Murali of Saroornagar, who charged the revenue officials of fraud to extend the undue benefit to Ramky.

news.title: Teams to be set up for structural audits of 60 condominiums in Gurugram
news.para: Deputy commissioner Nishant Yadav and other officials of the department of town and country planning (DTCP) on Wednesday held a discussion with RWA representatives and engineers to form a draft plan for audits of the societies.

news.title: Map fees hiked in Ghaziabad by over 5%, properties to cost more
news.para: Officials have attributed the hike to an increase in cost index under various heads like external development charges, sewer connection charges and inspection fees.

news.title: Maharashtra government raises ready reckoner rates by average 5%
news.para: In Mumbai municipal corporation area, the rates have been increased by an average of 2.34 per cent. ​​In Pune, Thane, Navi Mumbai corporations, the ready reckoner rates have been increased by 6.12, 9.48 and 8.90 per cent, respectively.

news.title: Goa CM moots delegation of technical nods for construction projects of upto 500 sq meters
news.para: Sawant said that the government also intends to take up online issuance of zoning certificates and NOCs under Section 49(6) of the TCP Act for registration of documents of plots.

news.title: Gurugram: NBCC Green View buyers demand refund of money, compensation
news.para: The homebuyers have sought refund of their investments along with a 15 per cent interest and a minimum compensation of Rs 25 lakh. The project is located in Gurugram, Haryana.

news.title: Hyderabad: Spiralling cost of fuel, raw materials hit realty sector
news.para: Rise in fuel prices in addition to the already spiralling cost of raw matierials such as cement, steel and sand has hit the cost of construction to the roof in the city.  Developers predict that this may escalate the real estate prices over the next few months.

news.title: Net leasing of office space in Jan-Mar jumps over two fold to 11.55 million sq ft
news.para: According to the data, net absorption of office space grew in all seven cities, barring Bengaluru that saw 30 per cent decline in the leasing numbers.

news.title: Case made out for hike in ready reckoner rate in Nagpur
news.para: Ready reckoner rates are the benchmark valuation of real estate. It is used for both, calculation of capital gains under income tax, and payment of stamp duty to the state government.
